      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "COSMIC GEM (4) wasn't beaten far at Bunbury two back before coming to the 1230m journey here last start as favourite, beaten 2.3L. Campbell hops on board today and he steps out to 1500m for the first time. Should get his chance from the draw and he can shed the maiden tag. TASMAN JEWEL (7) finished off strongly here two back when 2.9L off the winner before feeling the pinch late as a $2.90 favourite over the mile last start. Back to 1500m here may suit better and Azzopardi replaces the apprentice hoop. Can make her presence felt. GOD'LL GETYA (2) was slowly away on resumption but finished off strongly to be 1.6L off the winner. Out in trip for the first time may suit this son of Playing God and it wouldn't surprise to see him improve sharply. BIT TIRED ACTUALLY (9) is third-up now and can improve with this looking an easier assignment for her. HOPE TO ADMIRE (1) is better than he showed last start and can bounce back to his best.",
